ğŸŒ¤ï¸ Weather Now
ğŸ§­ Overview

Weather Now is a responsive web application built with React that allows users to quickly check the current weather conditions for any city around the world.
It displays temperature, wind speed, humidity, and an interactive map view of the selected location using React-Leaflet.

The app also supports dark mode, auto-suggestions for city search, and a clean adaptive layout for both desktop and mobile devices.

ğŸ¯ Objectives

The goal of this project is to create an interactive, user-friendly weather application that:

Provides accurate and real-time weather data.

Allows quick city-based searches with live suggestions.

Displays location visually on an interactive map.

Adapts seamlessly across desktop and mobile screens.

ğŸ—ï¸ Tech Stack
Purpose	Technology Used
Framework	React (Vite / React-Scripts)
