ğŸ§  How It Works

User enters a city name in the search box.

The app fetches latitude and longitude from the Open-Meteo Geocoding API.

Using the coordinates, it calls the Open-Meteo Weather API to retrieve real-time weather data.

Data is displayed dynamically, and a map marker appears on the Leaflet map.

Weather info (footer card) updates accordingly with appropriate weather icons.

Responsive CSS ensures proper scaling across all devices.

